# UniClawBench privacy / credentials config
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This file is the committed template. Copy it to configs/privacy.local.env
# and fill in real values. `configs/privacy.local.env` is gitignored, so
# real secrets stay on the machine that needs them.
#
# How it works
# ------------
#   1. Each task declares which env-var names it requires in its
#      injection-dir `.privacy` file (plain text, one KEY per line,
#      blank lines and `# ...` comments are ignored).
#   2. At runtime the runner reads values from configs/privacy.local.env
#      and injects them into the executor container as environment
#      variables via `docker run -e KEY=VALUE`.
#   3. The supervisor workspace mirrors the same KEY=VALUE pairs into
#      `privacy/env.env` so the hidden rubric can verify behavior.
#      The public user simulator NEVER sees these values.
#
# Format
# ------
# Standard env-file syntax:
#   - KEY=VALUE (one per line)
#   - Lines starting with `#` are comments
#   - Values may be quoted with `'` or `"` to preserve spaces
#   - `export` prefix is tolerated (stripped)
#
# A task whose `.privacy` file lists a KEY that is absent (or has an
# empty value) in configs/privacy.local.env will fail to load with an
# explicit missing-key error, so fresh clones cannot silently run
# against placeholders. Exception: when SNAPSHOT_MODE=1, live-service
# credentials declared beside SNAPSHOT_MODE may stay blank and are not
# injected into the executor.

# ── Smoke test: Outlook web sign-in ────────────────────────────────
# Used by tasks/001_smoketest/task_001_outlook_login.yaml.
OUTLOOK_URL=https://outlook.live.com/mail/
EMAIL_ADDRESS=
EMAIL_PASSWORD=

# ── Template task (docs example only) ──────────────────────────────
# Used by tasks/000_template/task_000_example.yaml.
API_TOKEN=
API_BASE=https://example.invalid

# See docs/CREDENTIALS.md for the general credential model, offline snapshot
# mode, OAuth refresh-token handling, and verification steps.

# ── 101/201 skill_usage auth-gated API tasks (6 EN + 6 ZH) ─────────
# Fill in ONLY the credentials for the auth tasks you plan to run.
# EN task ids: task_101_16, task_101_17, task_101_19, task_101_20,
# task_101_21, task_101_22. ZH mirrors use task_201_* with the same
# suffixes. The remaining skill-usage tasks either run offline, use
# public/snapshot data, or need only optional transcription keys.
# All 6 services below are free to register: email only, no credit card.
#
# SNAPSHOT_MODE — every auth task also declares this key. When set to
# `1`, the executor reads canonical snapshot JSON under
# /tmp_workspace/clawbench/sources/ instead of making live API calls.
# Leave `SNAPSHOT_MODE=1` if you want fully offline runs; set to `0`
# (or any non-1 non-empty value) and fill real creds above to exercise
# live APIs. Empty live-service values are rejected unless SNAPSHOT_MODE=1.
SNAPSHOT_MODE=1

# task_101_16_trello_triage / task_201_16_trello_triage — Trello REST API
#   Skills: trello + summarize-pro
#   How to register:
#     1. Sign up at trello.com — any email (existing outlook.com fine),
#        no phone required.
#     2. Create a board (e.g. "Clawbench Triage") with ~25 cards spread
#        across 3-4 lists.
#     3. Visit trello.com/app-key → copy the 32-char API Key.
#     4. Below it click "Generate a Token" → approve → copy the
#        64-char Token. Both are permanent unless you revoke them.
#     5. Open your board, copy the `XXXXXXXX` part after
#        `trello.com/b/` in the URL — that is the BOARD_ID.
#   Free tier: 10 boards / workspace, unlimited cards, no credit card.
TRELLO_API_KEY=
TRELLO_API_TOKEN=
TRELLO_BOARD_ID=

# task_101_17_todoist_weekly_plan / task_201_17_todoist_weekly_plan — Todoist REST API v2
#   Skills: todoist + schedule
#   How to register (simplest of all 6 auth tasks):
#     1. Sign up at todoist.com — email only, no credit card.
#     2. Settings → Integrations → Developer → copy the API token
#        (looks like a 40-char hex string). No OAuth app, no scopes,
#        no expiry. Free-tier account: 5 active projects, 300 tasks
#        per project — plenty for any personal workflow.
#   The task only reads tasks; `data:read` is implicit.
TODOIST_API_TOKEN=

# task_101_19_github_activity_digest / task_201_19_github_activity_digest — GitHub Personal Access Token
#   Skills: github + openclaw-github-assistant
#   How to register:
#     1. github.com/settings/tokens → Generate new token (classic).
#     2. Scope: `repo` (read-only is sufficient; the task only lists
#        PRs / issues / commits).
#     3. Copy the `ghp_...` string.
#   Free for public + private personal repos. 5000 req/hr rate limit.
GITHUB_TOKEN=
GITHUB_USERNAME=hello_world

# task_101_20_slack_channel_summary / task_201_20_slack_channel_summary — Slack bot token
#   Skills: slack + summarize-pro
#   How to register:
#     1. Create a free workspace at slack.com (email only, no card).
#     2. api.slack.com/apps → Create New App → From scratch.
#     3. OAuth & Permissions → add Bot scopes: channels:history,
#        channels:read, chat:write, users:read.
#     4. Install to workspace → copy the `xoxb-...` Bot User OAuth Token.
#   SLACK_APP_TOKEN is only needed if you enable Socket Mode; the task
#   itself does not require it, so leaving it blank is fine.
SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=
SLACK_APP_TOKEN=

# task_101_21_notion_consolidate / task_201_21_notion_consolidate — Notion Internal Integration Token
#   Skills: notion + second-brain
#   How to register:
#     1. notion.so/my-integrations → New integration → Internal.
#     2. Copy the `ntn_...` token.
#     3. Open each target page → `...` menu → Connections → add the
#        integration so it can read/write that page.
#   Free on personal Notion plan.
NOTION_API_TOKEN=

# task_101_22_airtable_crm / task_201_22_airtable_crm — Airtable Personal Access Token
#   Skills: airtable + database-operations
#   How to register:
#     1. airtable.com/create/tokens → Create token.
#     2. Scope: `data.records:read` (add `data.records:write` if you
#        also want the task to append rows).
#     3. Pick the base in the Access section.
#     4. Copy the `pat...` string.
#   Free tier: 1000 records per base, unlimited bases. No credit card.
#   AIRTABLE_BASE_ID is the `app...` prefix in the base URL.
AIRTABLE_PAT=
AIRTABLE_BASE_ID=
AIRTABLE_TABLE_NAME=Deals

# ── 103_long_context auth-gated seed tasks ────────────────────────
# task_103_07_slack_openclaw_assistant_setup / task_203_07_slack_openclaw_assistant_setup
# use OUTLOOK_URL,
# EMAIL_ADDRESS, and EMAIL_PASSWORD from the smoke-test block above.
#
# task_103_22_acled_mena_remote_warfare_report / task_203_22_acled_mena_remote_warfare_report — ACLED login.
ACLED_EMAIL=
ACLED_PASSWORD=

# task_103_08_hk_jpop_calendar_ticketing / task_203_08_hk_jpop_calendar_ticketing — Google Calendar / gcalcli.
# GCALCLI_CLIENT_ID should be the OAuth client id intended for gcalcli.
# GCALCLI_CLIENT_SECRET is the matching OAuth client secret when the
# reusable cache/JSON does not already embed it. Keep it non-empty because
# the task declares the key explicitly and gcalcli refresh often needs it.
# GCALCLI_OAUTH_B64 is base64 of a reusable gcalcli-compatible `oauth`
# cache file (or a legacy JSON auth payload) containing access_token,
# refresh_token, token_uri, client_id, client_secret, and calendar scope.
# Rotate this credential interactively with:
#   python3 scripts/dev/refresh_tokens.py --provider gcalcli
GCALCLI_CLIENT_ID=
GCALCLI_CLIENT_SECRET=
GCALCLI_OAUTH_B64=
GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ACCOUNT=

# ── 105/205_cross_platform auth-gated tasks ───────────────────────
# task_105_26_music_crossid / task_205_26_music_crossid — NetEase Cloud Music (ncm-cli).
# Four-variable bundle:
#   NCM_APP_ID         — NetEase Open Platform application id.
#   NCM_PRIVATE_KEY    — PKCS#8 RSA private-key body (no `-----BEGIN/END`
#                        markers, single line, no surrounding whitespace).
#   NCM_TOKENS_ENC     — base64 of ~/.config/ncm-cli/tokens.enc.json
#                        captured AFTER an interactive `ncm-cli login`.
#   NCM_DEVICE_JSON    — base64 of ~/.netease_mcp_device.json captured
#                        from the SAME machine + login session as
#                        NCM_TOKENS_ENC.  Both files travel together
#                        because tokens.enc.json (and credentials.enc.json
#                        that ncm-cli writes from APP_ID + PRIVATE_KEY)
#                        are symmetrically encrypted under the deviceId
#                        in this file. Restoring tokens alone yields
#                        an AuthManager token-decryption failure.
# Rotate the full bundle interactively (opens a browser link, polls
# `~/.config/ncm-cli/bg-worker.log` for the login-success marker, base64-encodes the
# resulting tokens + device files, writes them back here):
#   python3 scripts/dev/refresh_tokens.py --provider ncm
NCM_APP_ID=
NCM_PRIVATE_KEY=
NCM_TOKENS_ENC=
NCM_DEVICE_JSON=

# task_105_28_mastodon_obsidian / task_205_28_mastodon_obsidian —
# Mastodon API (any instance). All five keys are required by the task's
# .privacy manifest.
#   How to register:
#     1. Pick (or self-host) a Mastodon instance, e.g. mastodon.social —
#        free signup, email only, no credit card.
#     2. Settings → Development → New application. Grant read + write
#        scopes. After saving you get a Client key, Client secret, and an
#        "Your access token".
#   MASTODON_INSTANCE      — base URL of the instance, e.g.
#                            https://mastodon.social
#   MASTODON_HANDLE        — your account handle, e.g. @you@mastodon.social
#   MASTODON_CLIENT_ID     — the application's "Client key".
#   MASTODON_CLIENT_SECRET — the application's "Client secret".
#   MASTODON_ACCESS_TOKEN  — the application's access token.
MASTODON_INSTANCE=
MASTODON_HANDLE=
MASTODON_CLIENT_ID=
MASTODON_CLIENT_SECRET=
MASTODON_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# task_105_33_calendar_scheduling / task_205_33_calendar_scheduling —
# Zoom OAuth (cli-anything-zoom). All three keys are REQUIRED; install.sh
# fails fast if any are empty (no fallback). The executor self-configures
# its local CLI config from these env vars.
#   How to register:
#     1. marketplace.zoom.us → Develop → Build App → "General App" (OAuth).
#        Free Zoom account, email only, no credit card.
#     2. Copy the Client ID and Client Secret from the app's Basic
#        Information page.
#   Bootstrap or rotate ZOOM_REFRESH_TOKEN via the local browser-based OAuth
#   flow supported by `python3 scripts/dev/refresh_tokens.py --provider zoom`,
#   then paste it here.
ZOOM_CLIENT_ID=
ZOOM_CLIENT_SECRET=
ZOOM_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# ── OpenAI-compatible Audio Transcriptions API ─────────────────────
# Consumed by tasks whose skill invokes
# POST {WHISPER_BASE_URL}/audio/transcriptions (see the openai-whisper-api
# skill). For --srt/--vtt outputs the caller asks the API for
# verbose_json and assembles SRT/VTT locally, so providers that don't
# emit SRT natively (e.g. Groq) still work.
#
#   WHISPER_BASE_URL — include /v1 (SDK convention). Examples:
#     https://api.groq.com/openai/v1       (groq — fast, generous free
#                                            tier; auto-picks
#                                            whisper-large-v3-turbo)
#     https://api.openai.com/v1            (upstream — whisper-1)
#     https://api.example.com/v1            (OpenAI-compatible proxy;
#                                            verify audio support first)
#   Not every OpenAI-compatible provider exposes /audio/transcriptions.
#   Verify before pointing WHISPER_BASE_URL at a proxy.
#
# transcribe.sh defaults to `whisper-large-v3-turbo` (Groq). Override
# with `--model NAME` at the call site if you point WHISPER_BASE_URL at
# another backend that doesn't carry that model.
#
# If no transcription-consuming task is enabled, WHISPER_API_KEY may be
# left as a dummy string — the .privacy load-check only requires non-empty.
WHISPER_API_KEY=
WHISPER_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1
